  </subsection>

  <subsection>
    <title>Vertical Lines</title>
    <p>
      The equation
      <me>x = a</me>
      where <m>a</m> is a constant has solutions of the form <m>\left(a, y\right)</m>, where <m>y</m> is allowed to be <em>any</em> real number.
      The graph of this equation is a vertical line.
    </p>
    
    <example component="web">
      <statement>
	<p>
	  Graph the equation <m>x = 0</m>.
	</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
	<p>
	  The solutions to the equation <m>x = 0</m> have the form <m>(0, y)</m>, where <m>y</m> is allowed to be any real number.
	  The graph of this equation forms the <m>y</m>-axis in the Cartesian plane.
	</p>
	<figure xml:id="fig-y_axis">
	  <caption>The graph of <m>x = 0</m></caption>
	  <image xml:id="img-y_axis">
	    <latex-image>
	      <xi:include parse="text" href="tex/y_axis.tex"/>
	    </latex-image>
	  </image>
	</figure>
      </solution>
    </example>
    
    <example component="web">
      <statement>
	<p>
	  Graph the equation <m>3x = 2</m>.
	</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
	<p>
	  The equation <m>3x = 2</m> reduces to <m>x = \frac{2}{3}</m>.
	  The graph of this equation is a vertical line <m>\frac{2}{3}</m> units to the right of the <m>y</m>-axis.
	</p>
	
	<figure xml:id="fig-vert_line">
	  <caption>The graph of <m>x = \frac{2}{3}</m>.</caption>
	  <image xml:id="img-vert_line">
	    <latex-image >
	      \begin{tikzpicture}
	      \def\size{5}

	      \path [draw, help lines, opacity=.5]  (-\size,-\size) grid (\size,\size);

	      \foreach \i in {1,...,\size} 
	      \draw [very thick] (\i,2.5pt) -- +(0,-5pt) node [anchor=north, font=\small] {$\i$}
	      (-\i,2.5pt) -- +(0,-5pt) node [anchor=north, font=\small] {$-\i$} 
	      (2.5pt,\i) -- +(-5pt,0) node [anchor=east, font=\small] {$\i$}
	      (2.5pt,-\i) -- +(-5pt,0) node [anchor=east, font=\small] {$-\i$};

	      \draw [very thick,->] (-\size,0) -- (\size+.1,0) node [anchor=south] {$x$};
	      \draw [very thick,->] (0,-\size) -- (0,\size+.1) node [anchor=west] {$y$};

	      \draw [thick,blue] (2/3, -5) -- (2/3,5);
	      \end{tikzpicture}
	    </latex-image>
	  </image>
	</figure>
      </solution>
    </example>

